        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>RegOffset</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>u32</type>
          <declname>Data</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function writes a value to a MIPI DSI2 Rx Subsystem register. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>A 32 bit write is performed. If the component is implemented in a smaller width, only the least significant data is written.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the base address of the XDsiRxSs core instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>RegOffset</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the register offset of the register (defined at the top of this file) to be written. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the 32-bit value to write into the register.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>None.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>None </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
